Boolean attributes in HTML are attributes that represent true or false values based on their presence or absence. If a boolean attribute is present, it is considered true; if it is absent, it is considered false.

<!-- Global boolean attribute -->
<div hidden>This element is hidden.</div>

<!-- Non-global boolean attribute (used with form elements) -->
<input type="text" disabled readonly required>


